description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Senior Neonatal Support Worker to join our team to enhance the level of care and support given to new mothers/parents of our neonatal patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you experienced in supporting the care of neonates and their families in a clinical setting and wish to bring your skill, care and compassion to support them at GOSH?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With a particular focus on supporting infant feeding, including breastfeeding, you will need to be competent and confident in giving evidence-based advice. You will provide effective person-centred care through planning, organising and prioritising your care delivery, whilst being supported by the clinical team under direct and indirect supervision. You will also be able to develop and learn within your role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have a passion for caring and proven experience in helping new mothers/parents navigate their journey through early parenthood, we want to hear from you!&lt;/p&gt;
